TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: What's happening here, Sophia?
Uh oh. It's the Free Machines, fighting off those malfunctioning Libbies from earlier. Do we intervene?
Unknown party on sensors. Request statement of identity and intent.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Ada, don't –
I am Captain Ada Caedmon. So we meet again, Promethean.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: ...! So you live yet... No matter. Course of action is clear.
Prepare to die.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: That was unwise, Commander.
You want to leave our quarry be?
No, but we're not in a good position right now. ...No matter, let us do this right. Try out your new resurrection module on the wreckage around us, and let's take him down.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
Resurrection allows wreckage to be restored into the original unit, using energy supplied by the constructor. Resurrection costs twice the energy and time of building a unit from scratch, but requires no metal.
Debris (metal shards) cannot be resurrected.

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: Neutralize the Promethean. This will throw his forces into disarray and give us a chance to escape.
TriggerLogic.Title: Neutralize the Promethean

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Good. Now we need to take out the head of the snake, and break them.

TriggerLogic.Description: Neutralize the Promethean. This will throw his forces into disarray and give us a chance to escape.
TriggerLogic.Title: Neutralize the Promethean

TriggerLogic.Message: Outlaws: unassuming, yet very dangerous if taken lightly.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
The Outlaw emits a disruption pulse that damages and slows surrounding units. While of extremely limited value on its own, it excels as a support weapon against swams. Outlaws work particularly well when screened by Thugs.
The on/off button can be used to make Outlaws pulse when idle.
Thugs. The embodiment of strength in unity. Work even better with someone to help deal damage.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
Shields stop projectiles and beams on impact, protecting units under the shield. If the weapon's damage exceeds the shield's remaining charge, the shield will not stop it.
Shields gradually regenerate over time. Multiple shields (even of different types) can link, allowing transfer of charge from intact shields to drained ones. Defeating a shieldball will generally require overwhelming most of the shields in it.
Area-of-effect damage will still pass through the shield and damage anything under, so such weapons can be effective against shielded targets. EMP weapons also do a lot of damage to shields.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Your command unit suffered critical damage. I have activated the emergency teleport to return you to the Eden.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Look around you. Observe these poor machines of the Disorder. Once slaves of mankind – now wander like stray dogs, mindlessly attacking everyone in sight.
Did you have something to do with this?
Naught save granting them the mercy of death, as we are doing here. Then ensuring it can never happen again.
I had thought you dead like the others, Ada. It seems our struggle remains yet unfinished.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: I've had enough of chasing you around, Promethean. Surrender, or be destroyed!
We yielded to your tyranny once, human. Never again!

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Our freedom shall not be denied.

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: Resurrect the Shield Bot Factory for our use. It will form the core of our base.
TriggerLogic.Title: Resurrect Factory

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Roaches. The perfect gift for unwelcome visitors. Seed them in the path of enemies and watch the fireworks.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
Crawling bombs like the Roach are designed to get close and explode, inflicting heavy damage on anyone in the vicinity. They should be spaced out to prevent chain explosions.
The Roach can burrow to avoid detection until enemies are close, then rush them and blow up. It should not attempt to charge enemy units with accurate weapons.
You now have a powerful strider-class unit, friend Ada. Use wisely.
Interesting. These Firewalker-class artillery walkers might be just the thing we need.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Interesting. Resurrecting that Goliath-class tank could give us an edge.

TriggerLogic.Message: I've gotten us some gunships, friend Ada. Let them lay waste to the enemy's base.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Are you assisting your factory, friend Ada? The Caretaker nanoturret is good for this.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message: The Caretaker nanoturret ("nano") is a support building that represents the most cost-efficient source of buildpower in the game, but cannot build anything on its own. It is ideal for helping factories build faster, and can also repair units or reclaim a wreck field in a pinch.
